Aim: Write a trigger to demonstrate the use of Row level trigger and Statement level trigger.

Solution:
Statement-Level Trigger:
CREATE OR REPLACE TRIGGER trig_upt_student
BEFORE UPDATE ON student
BEGIN
    DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('This is a statement-level trigger that got fired');
END;
/

Row-Level Trigger:
CREATE OR REPLACE TRIGGER trig_upt_student
BEFORE UPDATE ON student FOR EACH ROW
BEGIN
    DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Row-level trigger got fired');
END;
/
Explanation:
•	Statement-Level Trigger:
o	The trig_upt_student trigger is a statement-level trigger that fires once before an UPDATE statement on the student table.
o	It displays a message when the trigger is activated.
•	Row-Level Trigger:
o	Another trig_upt_student trigger is a row-level trigger that fires before each row is updated in the student table.
o	It displays a message for each row that is affected by the UPDATE statement.
Outcome: This practical demonstrates the difference between row-level and statement-level triggers, teaching students how to use each type effectively.



1.Statement level Trigger
CREATE OR REPLACE TRIGGER tri_st
BEFORE UPDATE ON st_info
BEGIN
    DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('This is statement level trigger fixed');
END;
/
SET SERVEROUTPUT ON;
UPDATE st_info
SET total = sub1 + sub2 + sub3 + sub4;
SHOW ERRORS;#for compilation errors


2.Row level Trigger
CREATE OR REPLACE TRIGGER tri_row
BEFORE UPDATE ON st_info
FOR EACH ROW
BEGIN
    DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('This is row level trigger fixed');
END;
/
SET SERVEROUTPUT ON;
UPDATE st_info
SET total = sub1 + sub2 + sub3 + sub4
WHERE sub1 > 80;


3.Trigger for Sub marks validation
CREATE OR REPLACE TRIGGER tri_ins
BEFORE INSERT ON st_info
FOR EACH ROW
BEGIN
   IF (:NEW.sub1 < 0 OR :NEW.sub1 > 100) THEN
      DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Invalid marks in Subject 1');   
   ELSIF (:NEW.sub2 < 0 OR :NEW.sub2 > 100) THEN
      DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Invalid marks in Subject 2');      
   ELSIF (:NEW.sub3 < 0 OR :NEW.sub3 > 100) THEN
      DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Invalid marks in Subject 3');      
   ELSIF (:NEW.sub4 < 0 OR :NEW.sub4 > 100) THEN
      DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Invalid marks in Subject 4');      
   ELSE
      DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('All subject marks are valid');
   END IF;
END;
/
